#### Q41. What do you need to change about this code to get it to run?

```js
class clock extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return <h1>Look at the time: {this.props.time}</h1>;
  }
}
```

- %OPTION% Add quotes around the return value
- %OPTION% Remove `this`
- %OPTION% Remove the render method
- %OPTION% Capitalize `clock`

Read [this article](https://reactjs.org/docs/jsx-in-depth.html#html-tags-vs.-react-components)**Explanation:** In JSX, lower-case tag names are considered to be HTML tags.

#### Q44. How do you invoke setDone only when component mounts, using hooks?

```javascript
function MyComponent(props) {
  const [done, setDone] = useState(false);

  return <h1>Done: {done}</h1>;
}
```

- %OPTION% `useEffect(() => { setDone(true); });`
- %OPTION% `useEffect(() => { setDone(true); }, []);`
- %OPTION% `useEffect(() => { setDone(true); }, [setDone]);`
- %OPTION% `useEffect(() => { setDone(true); }, [done, setDone]);`

#### Q48. What will happen when this useEffect Hook is executed, assuming name is not already equal to John?

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  setName('John');
}, [name]);
```

- %OPTION% It will cause an error immediately.
- %OPTION% It will execute the code inside the function, but only after waiting to ensure that no other component is accessing the name variable.
- %OPTION% It will update the value of name once and not run again until name is changed from the outside.
- %OPTION% It will cause an infinite loop.

#### Q50. You have created a new method in a class component called handleClick, but it is not working. Which code is missing?

```javascript
